Welcome to the Inner Confidence Podcast, where we bring you men's, dating, and lifestyle advice that doesn't suck. In today's episode, host Robbie Kramer delves into the topic of assumption stacking, a technique used in the London Day game model to make engaging conversations with women. Joined by a guest speaker, they discuss the power of assumption stacking and how it can help create meaningful connections even in challenging situations. From cold reads to clever openers like the horse girl question, Robbie and his guest explore various strategies to keep the conversation flowing and build attraction. So, if you're ready to boost your conversational skills and deepen your understanding of the day game approach, tune in to this week's episode of the Inner Confidence Podcast. Let's get started!

Show Notes:

[00:01:23] Structured London Day Game Model for successful interactions. Assumption stacking replaces questions, increasing engagement.

[00:04:36] Entertaining opener: teasing about being horse-obsessed.

[00:07:04] Cold reading is effective for sparking interest. Stacking keeps the conversation flowing and energized.

[00:09:29] Repeat line until perfect, then improvise. Open, close, practice.

[00:14:09] Day game tactics and overcoming approach anxiety.

[00:17:05] Discuss, improve, find own spin, focus.
